---
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>mosoptics — Computer Vision Step Library for Mosaigo</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="mosoptics is a computer vision step library for Mosaigo. Face detection, gaze estimation, stereo capture, and GPU-accelerated inference as composable, typed pipeline steps."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="topnav">
      <a href="/staging/" class="topnav-logo">
        <img src="/images/mozzy-icon.webp" alt="mosaigo" />
        mosaigo
      </a>
      <div class="topnav-links">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="topnav-link">Docs</a>
        <a href="/staging/mosoptics/" class="topnav-link active">mosoptics</a>
        <a href="/staging/mosii/" class="topnav-link">mosii</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-badge"><span class="dot"></span> Go + CGo &middot; GoCV &middot; ONNX Runtime</div>
      <h1>See the world through <span class="accent">pipelines</span></h1>
      <p class="tagline">mosoptics is a computer vision step library for Mosaigo (mosaic-go). Face detection, gaze estimation, stereo capture, and GPU-accelerated inference, all as composable, typed pipeline steps.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/docs-mosoptics/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Docs</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-install">
        <span class="prompt">$</span> go get github.com/mosaigoio/mosoptics@latest
      </div>
      <img src="/images/mozzy-eyes2.webp" alt="Computer vision with gaze tracking" class="hero-img" loading="lazy" />
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">The challenge</div>
      <h2>Vision is hard. Experimentation should be easy.</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Real-time computer vision means juggling cameras, models, GPU drivers, frame rates, and latency. mosoptics handles the plumbing so you can focus on the science.</p>
      <div class="diff-grid">
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon primary">&#128247;</div>
          <h3>Parallel Camera Streams</h3>
          <p>Run multiple cameras simultaneously with independent pipelines. Stereo capture, multi-angle recording, or mixed resolution. Each stream is an engine with its own frame rate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon accent">&#9889;</div>
          <h3>GPU-Accelerated Inference</h3>
          <p>ONNX Runtime with CUDA, TensorRT on NVIDIA Jetson, CoreML/Metal on Apple M-series. Build-tag gated: same step code, hardware-specific acceleration at build time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon success">&#128257;</div>
          <h3>Rapid Model Experimentation</h3>
          <p>Swap detection models by changing one step name. UltraFace or MediaPipe for face detection? L2CS-Net or 6DRepNet for gaze? Try both, compare with MarkTime, keep the winner.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon light">&#128065;</div>
          <h3>Full Gaze Pipeline</h3>
          <p>Camera capture, face detection, face mesh, eye region extraction, pupil tracking, gaze estimation, stereo triangulation, focal point mapping. Every stage is a replaceable step.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon error">&#127919;</div>
          <h3>60-120fps Real-Time</h3>
          <p>Pre-allocated frame buffers, zero-copy payload passing, batched CGo calls. Designed for Jetson Orin Nano at 60fps, Apple M-series at 120fps.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon muted">&#128300;</div>
          <h3>Studio Visualization</h3>
          <p>Live pipeline visualization showing per-step frame rates, latency heatmaps, and annotated video output. Debug gaze vectors and face mesh overlays in real time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="showcase-row">
        <div class="showcase-card">
          <img src="/images/portfolio-hardware.webp" alt="Edge device with stereo camera" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Edge-First Design</h3>
            <p>Built for Jetson Orin Nano, Raspberry Pi, and embedded Linux with stereo camera support.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="showcase-card">
          <img src="/images/portfolio-studio.webp" alt="Studio observability dashboard" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Live Studio Dashboard</h3>
            <p>Real-time pipeline visualization with per-step latency heatmaps and annotated video output.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-centered">
      <div class="section-label">Packages</div>
      <h2>Every vision task is a step</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">mosoptics packages map directly to pipeline steps. Import what you need, compose the pipeline you want.</p>
      <div class="pkg-grid">
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">cam/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Camera enumeration, V4L2, macOS capture</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">frame/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Frame types, DualFrame, stereo pairs</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">face/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Face detection, mesh, recognition</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">eye/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Eye region, pupil tracking, corneal reflection</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">gaze/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Gaze estimation, calibration, smoothing</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">pose/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Head pose estimation, yaw/pitch/roll</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">stereo/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Stereo triangulation, camera calibration</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name">onnx/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">ONNX Runtime wrapper, model loading</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pkg-row">
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name accent">gpu/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">TensorRT, VPI, CUDA (build-tag gated)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name accent">display/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Display steps, annotated overlays</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name accent">record/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">Recording, playback, session management</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <div class="pkg-name accent">stream/</div>
          <div class="pkg-desc">MJPEG, RTSP, HLS streaming</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">AI models</div>
      <h2>Plug in any model, compare everything</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">mosoptics wraps each model in a standard Mosaigo step. Swap models by name, measure with MarkTime, keep the one that works.</p>
      <div class="eco-grid">
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge primary">face detection</div>
          <h3>UltraFace &middot; MediaPipe &middot; SCRFD</h3>
          <p>Lightweight face detection optimized for edge devices. UltraFace at ~2ms/frame on Jetson, MediaPipe with full 468-point mesh. Each model is a drop-in step replacement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge accent">gaze estimation</div>
          <h3>L2CS-Net &middot; 6DRepNet &middot; GazeML</h3>
          <p>Appearance-based gaze estimation from eye crops. L2CS-Net for direct gaze vector, 6DRepNet for head pose, combined for focal point estimation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge success">hardware targets</div>
          <h3>Jetson Orin &middot; Apple M-series &middot; x86 CUDA</h3>
          <p>Same pipeline definition, hardware-optimized execution. TensorRT on Jetson (INT8/FP16), CoreML on macOS, CUDA on workstations. Build tags select the right backend.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-centered">
      <div class="section-label">Architecture</div>
      <h2>Built on Mosaigo, focused on vision</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">mosoptics is a collection of Go packages that each export Mosaigo steps. The CGo boundary lives here. Mosaigo stays pure Go.</p>
      <div class="arch-visual">
        <div class="arch-layer accent">
          Your Application <span class="desc">mosii, research tools, custom products</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-arrow">imports &#8595;</div>
        <div class="arch-layer primary">
          mosoptics <span class="desc">cam, face, eye, gaze, pose, stereo, onnx, gpu (CGo)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-arrow">built on &#8595;</div>
        <div class="arch-layer deep">
          Mosaigo <span class="desc">Engine, pipeline, typed steps, topics, config, validation, Studio (pure Go)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="arch-caption">mosoptics contains all CGo dependencies. Mosaigo never touches CGo. Your application chooses which mosoptics packages to import.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">12+</div><div class="label">Vision step packages</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">60-120</div><div class="label">FPS target</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">3</div><div class="label">GPU backends</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">0</div><div class="label">Allocations in Process()</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">Open</div><div class="label">Source</div></div>
    </div>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Start building vision pipelines</h2>
      <p>Browse the step catalog, set up your cameras, or explore the architecture.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/docs-mosoptics/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Docs</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="/staging/">mosaigo</a>
        <a href="/docs-mosoptics/">Docs</a>
      </div>
      <p>Part of the <a href="/staging/">mosaigoio</a> family</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
